Daiwa Securities America Inc, whollyowned by Daiwa Securities Co Ltd, of Tokyo, received approvalto acquire a seat on the Toronto Stock Exchange for 361,000Canadian dlrs, the exchange said.    Approval was granted by the exchange's board of governorsand is the first acquisition of an exchange seat by a Japanesecompany, it said.    The purchase price is the highest ever paid for an exchangeseat, it added.    Daiwa acquired the exchange seat from Andras ResearchCapital Inc, the Toronto Stock Exchange said.    Daiwa now intends to apply for exchange membership, whichwill be subject to approval by other exchange members and theOntario Securities Commission, it said. Reuter&#3;